29#ifndef OT_LAYOUT_COMMON_COVERAGE_HH
30#define OT_LAYOUT_COMMON_COVERAGE_HH

32#include "../types.hh"
33#include "CoverageFormat1.hh"
34#include "CoverageFormat2.hh"

36namespace OT {
37namespace Layout {
38namespace Common {

40template<typename Iterator>
41static inline void Coverage_serialize (hb_serialize_context_t *c,
42 Iterator it);
43
44struct Coverage
45{
46
47 protected:
48 union {
49 HBUINT16 format; /* Format identifier */
50 CoverageFormat1_3<SmallTypes> format1;
51 CoverageFormat2_4<SmallTypes> format2;
52#ifndef HB_NO_BEYOND_64K
53 CoverageFormat1_3<MediumTypes>format3;
54 CoverageFormat2_4<MediumTypes>format4;
55#endif
56 } u;
57 public:
58 DEFINE_SIZE_UNION (2, format);
59
60 bool sanitize (hb_sanitize_context_t *c) const
61 {
62 TRACE_SANITIZE (this);
63 if (!u.format.sanitize (c)) return_trace (false);
64 switch (u.format)
65 {
66 case 1: return_trace (u.format1.sanitize (c));
67 case 2: return_trace (u.format2.sanitize (c));
68#ifndef HB_NO_BEYOND_64K
69 case 3: return_trace (u.format3.sanitize (c));
70 case 4: return_trace (u.format4.sanitize (c));
71#endif
72 default:return_trace (true);
73 }
74 }
75
76 /* Has interface. */
77 unsigned operator [] (hb_codepoint_t k) const { return get (k); }
78 bool has (hb_codepoint_t k) const { return (*this)[k] != NOT_COVERED; }
79 /* Predicate. */
80 bool operator () (hb_codepoint_t k) const { return has (k); }
81
82 unsigned int get (hb_codepoint_t k) const { return get_coverage (glyph_id: k); }
83 unsigned int get_coverage (hb_codepoint_t glyph_id) const
84 {
85 switch (u.format) {
86 case 1: return u.format1.get_coverage (glyph_id);
87 case 2: return u.format2.get_coverage (glyph_id);
88#ifndef HB_NO_BEYOND_64K
89 case 3: return u.format3.get_coverage (glyph_id);
90 case 4: return u.format4.get_coverage (glyph_id);
91#endif
92 default:return NOT_COVERED;
93 }
94 }
95
96 unsigned get_population () const
97 {
98 switch (u.format) {
99 case 1: return u.format1.get_population ();
100 case 2: return u.format2.get_population ();
101#ifndef HB_NO_BEYOND_64K
102 case 3: return u.format3.get_population ();
103 case 4: return u.format4.get_population ();
104#endif
105 default:return NOT_COVERED;
106 }
107 }
108
109 template <typename Iterator,
110 hb_requires (hb_is_sorted_source_of (Iterator, hb_codepoint_t))>
111 bool serialize (hb_serialize_context_t *c, Iterator glyphs)
112 {
113 TRACE_SERIALIZE (this);
114 if (unlikely (!c->extend_min (this))) return_trace (false);
115
116 unsigned count = 0;
117 unsigned num_ranges = 0;
118 hb_codepoint_t last = (hb_codepoint_t) -2;
119 for (auto g: glyphs)
120 {
121 if (last + 1 != g)
122 num_ranges++;
123 last = g;
124 count++;
125 }
126 u.format = count <= num_ranges * 3 ? 1 : 2;
127
128#ifndef HB_NO_BEYOND_64K
129 if (count && last > 0xFFFFu)
130 u.format += 2;
131#endif
132
133 switch (u.format)
134 {
135 case 1: return_trace (u.format1.serialize (c, glyphs));
136 case 2: return_trace (u.format2.serialize (c, glyphs));
137#ifndef HB_NO_BEYOND_64K
138 case 3: return_trace (u.format3.serialize (c, glyphs));
139 case 4: return_trace (u.format4.serialize (c, glyphs));
140#endif
141 default:return_trace (false);
142 }
143 }
144
145 bool subset (hb_subset_context_t *c) const
146 {
147 TRACE_SUBSET (this);
148 auto it =
149 + iter ()
150 | hb_take (c->plan->source->get_num_glyphs ())
151 | hb_filter (c->plan->glyph_map_gsub)
152 | hb_map_retains_sorting (c->plan->glyph_map_gsub)
153 ;
154
155 // Cache the iterator result as it will be iterated multiple times
156 // by the serialize code below.
157 hb_sorted_vector_t<hb_codepoint_t> glyphs (it);
158 Coverage_serialize (c: c->serializer, it: glyphs.iter ());
159 return_trace (bool (glyphs));
160 }
161
162 bool intersects (const hb_set_t *glyphs) const
163 {
164 switch (u.format)
165 {
166 case 1: return u.format1.intersects (glyphs);
167 case 2: return u.format2.intersects (glyphs);
168#ifndef HB_NO_BEYOND_64K
169 case 3: return u.format3.intersects (glyphs);
170 case 4: return u.format4.intersects (glyphs);
171#endif
172 default:return false;
173 }
174 }
175 bool intersects_coverage (const hb_set_t *glyphs, unsigned int index) const
176 {
177 switch (u.format)
178 {
179 case 1: return u.format1.intersects_coverage (glyphs, index);
180 case 2: return u.format2.intersects_coverage (glyphs, index);
181#ifndef HB_NO_BEYOND_64K
182 case 3: return u.format3.intersects_coverage (glyphs, index);
183 case 4: return u.format4.intersects_coverage (glyphs, index);
184#endif
185 default:return false;
186 }
187 }
188
189 /* Might return false if array looks unsorted.
190 * Used for faster rejection of corrupt data. */
191 template <typename set_t>
192 bool collect_coverage (set_t *glyphs) const
193 {
194 switch (u.format)
195 {
196 case 1: return u.format1.collect_coverage (glyphs);
197 case 2: return u.format2.collect_coverage (glyphs);
198#ifndef HB_NO_BEYOND_64K
199 case 3: return u.format3.collect_coverage (glyphs);
200 case 4: return u.format4.collect_coverage (glyphs);
201#endif
202 default:return false;
203 }
204 }
205
206 template <typename IterableOut,
207 hb_requires (hb_is_sink_of (IterableOut, hb_codepoint_t))>
208 void intersect_set (const hb_set_t &glyphs, IterableOut&& intersect_glyphs) const
209 {
210 switch (u.format)
211 {
212 case 1: return u.format1.intersect_set (glyphs, intersect_glyphs);
213 case 2: return u.format2.intersect_set (glyphs, intersect_glyphs);
214#ifndef HB_NO_BEYOND_64K
215 case 3: return u.format3.intersect_set (glyphs, intersect_glyphs);
216 case 4: return u.format4.intersect_set (glyphs, intersect_glyphs);
217#endif
218 default:return ;
219 }
220 }
221
222 struct iter_t : hb_iter_with_fallback_t<iter_t, hb_codepoint_t>
223 {
224 static constexpr bool is_sorted_iterator = true;
225 iter_t (const Coverage &c_ = Null (Coverage))
226 {
227 hb_memset (s: this, c: 0, n: sizeof (*this));
228 format = c_.u.format;
229 switch (format)
230 {
231 case 1: u.format1.init (c_: c_.u.format1); return;
232 case 2: u.format2.init (c_: c_.u.format2); return;
233#ifndef HB_NO_BEYOND_64K
234 case 3: u.format3.init (c_.u.format3); return;
235 case 4: u.format4.init (c_.u.format4); return;
236#endif
237 default: return;
238 }
239 }
240 bool __more__ () const
241 {
242 switch (format)
243 {
244 case 1: return u.format1.__more__ ();
245 case 2: return u.format2.__more__ ();
246#ifndef HB_NO_BEYOND_64K
247 case 3: return u.format3.__more__ ();
248 case 4: return u.format4.__more__ ();
249#endif
250 default:return false;
251 }
252 }
253 void __next__ ()
254 {
255 switch (format)
256 {
257 case 1: u.format1.__next__ (); break;
258 case 2: u.format2.__next__ (); break;
259#ifndef HB_NO_BEYOND_64K
260 case 3: u.format3.__next__ (); break;
261 case 4: u.format4.__next__ (); break;
262#endif
263 default: break;
264 }
265 }
266 typedef hb_codepoint_t __item_t__;
267 __item_t__ __item__ () const { return get_glyph (); }
268
269 hb_codepoint_t get_glyph () const
270 {
271 switch (format)
272 {
273 case 1: return u.format1.get_glyph ();
274 case 2: return u.format2.get_glyph ();
275#ifndef HB_NO_BEYOND_64K
276 case 3: return u.format3.get_glyph ();
277 case 4: return u.format4.get_glyph ();
278#endif
279 default:return 0;
280 }
281 }
282 bool operator != (const iter_t& o) const
283 {
284 if (unlikely (format != o.format)) return true;
285 switch (format)
286 {
287 case 1: return u.format1 != o.u.format1;
288 case 2: return u.format2 != o.u.format2;
289#ifndef HB_NO_BEYOND_64K
290 case 3: return u.format3 != o.u.format3;
291 case 4: return u.format4 != o.u.format4;
292#endif
293 default:return false;
294 }
295 }
296 iter_t __end__ () const
297 {
298 iter_t it = {};
299 it.format = format;
300 switch (format)
301 {
302 case 1: it.u.format1 = u.format1.__end__ (); break;
303 case 2: it.u.format2 = u.format2.__end__ (); break;
304#ifndef HB_NO_BEYOND_64K
305 case 3: it.u.format3 = u.format3.__end__ (); break;
306 case 4: it.u.format4 = u.format4.__end__ (); break;
307#endif
308 default: break;
309 }
310 return it;
311 }
312
313 private:
314 unsigned int format;
315 union {
316#ifndef HB_NO_BEYOND_64K
317 CoverageFormat2_4<MediumTypes>::iter_t format4; /* Put this one first since it's larger; helps shut up compiler. */
318 CoverageFormat1_3<MediumTypes>::iter_t format3;
319#endif
320 CoverageFormat2_4<SmallTypes>::iter_t format2; /* Put this one first since it's larger; helps shut up compiler. */
321 CoverageFormat1_3<SmallTypes>::iter_t format1;
322 } u;
323 };
324 iter_t iter () const { return iter_t (*this); }
325};
326
327template<typename Iterator>
328static inline void
329Coverage_serialize (hb_serialize_context_t *c,
330 Iterator it)
331{ c->start_embed<Coverage> ()->serialize (c, it); }
332
333}
334}
335}
